"Lacking much flavor.  Kind of blah."
"Overall / Drinkability: This one throws me for how to characterize it. It has some definite Belgian style flavor notes, but has some aspects of a Belgian Wit and I'm not sure if it has any real aspects of a Cream ale or not. Maybe in regard to the mouthfeel. So since it defies easy characterization, I'll just say that as a beer, it's easily drinkable (went well with Pork tacos and salad) and flavorful enough that I think it would pair with a wide range of food. Overall, it's a definitely above average beer but it's hard to rate per a style because it's a hybrid."
